Ensure that the [`searchAccounts`](command:_github.copilot.openSymbolFromReferences?%5B%7B%22%24mid%22%3A1%2C%22path%22%3A%22%2FUsers%2Fthbui%2FDocuments%2FSalesforce%2FOrder-Management-System%2F.sfdx%2Ftypings%2Flwc%2Fapex%2FQueryController.d.ts%22%2C%22scheme%22%3A%22file%22%7D%2C%7B%22line%22%3A1%2C%22character%22%3A2%7D%5D ".sfdx/typings/lwc/apex/QueryController.d.ts") method returns the necessary fields.

```apex
public with sharing class QueryController {
    @AuraEnabled
    public static List<Patient__c> searchAccounts(String searchTerm) {
        String query = 'SELECT firstName__c, mi__c, lastName__c, dob__c, sex__c, mrn__c, address__c, city__c, country__c, zipCode__c, phone__c, state__c, email__c FROM Patient__c WHERE ' +
                       'firstName__c LIKE :searchTerm OR lastName__c LIKE :searchTerm or address__c LIKE: searchTerm or email__c LIKE:searchTerm or mrn__c LIKE: searchTerm';
        return Database.query(query);
    }
}
```

With these changes, when you search for a patient and select a row from the data table, the form fields will be populated with the selected patient's information.

